class.description:
[ImportExporter] converts the imported, engine-optimized resources stored inside a Godot PCK archive back to their original editable source formats - for example, converting [code].ctex[/code] textures back to [code].png[/code], [code].oggstr[/code] audio back to [code].ogg[/code], and so on. It operates on a project that has already been loaded into [GDRESettings].
Load a project with [method GDRESettings.load_project] before calling any [ImportExporter] methods.
[codeblock]
var settings = Engine.get_singleton("GDRESettings")
var err = settings.load_project(PackedStringArray(["path/to/game.pck"]))
if err != OK:
    push_error("Failed to load project")
    return

var exporter = ImportExporter.new()
err = exporter.export_imports("/path/to/output_dir")
if err == OK:
    var report = exporter.get_report()
    print("Export complete: ", report)

settings.unload_project()
[/codeblock]
